experiment 1.1 contain duplicate (LEETCODE 217)

AIM:Given an integer array nums, return true if any value appears at least twice in the array, and return false if every element is distinct.

ALGO:
1.Read the array nums.
2.Sort the array in ascending order.
3.Traverse the array from index 1 to n-1.
4.Compare the current element with the previous element.
5.If they are equal, return true (duplicate found).
6.If the loop finishes without finding duplicates, return false.

CODE:
class Solution {
public:
    bool containsDuplicate(vector<int>& nums) {
        sort(nums.begin(), nums.end());

        for (int i = 1; i < nums.size(); i++) {
            if (nums[i] == nums[i - 1]) {
                return true;
            }
        }

        return false;
    }
};


EXPERIMENT 1.2 contain duplicate-2 (LEETCODE 219)

AIM:Given an integer array nums and an integer k, return true if there are two distinct indices i and j in the array such that nums[i] == nums[j] and abs(i - j) <= k.

ALGO:
1.Create an empty hash map mp.
2.Traverse the array from index 0 to n-1.
3.If the current element already exists in the map:
4.Calculate the distance between the current index and its previous index.
5.If the distance is less than or equal to k, return true.
6.Update the current element's index in the map.
7.If no such pair is found, return false.

CODE:
class Solution {
public:
    bool containsNearbyDuplicate(vector<int>& nums, int k) {
        unordered_map<int, int> mp;

        for (int i = 0; i < nums.size(); i++) {
            if (mp.count(nums[i])) {
                if (i - mp[nums[i]] <= k) {
                    return true;
                }
            }
            mp[nums[i]] = i;
        }

        return false;
    }
};
